ruby_in_practice
================

Demonstrating how to create and deploy Ruby Gems (chapter 8).

The skeleton was created by running:

  newgem ruby_in_practice --simple

To create a new gem, run:

  rake package

To install the gem:

  gem install pkg/ruby_in_practice-0.1.0.gem

You can now require the gem from your Ruby program:

  require 'ruby_in_practice'

Or run it from the command line:

  ruby_in_practice
